This village is small enough to walk around.

Queidersbach is just a few kilometres away from the city of Kaiserslautern and is the perfect place for bicycle or hiking tours, cultural, sportive, swimming and leisure activities.

Hahnenfest (Chicken Fest) in Queidersbach, Germany: A Festival Not to Be Missed!
The fest is traditionally held the second Sunday in July. There are carnival rides for the children and candy trailers. You can purchase the various foods, bratwurst, fries and the famous chicken.
There are two terrific bakeries, fresh bread, pretzels, and pasteries.  There is also a grocery store.  The local butcher has a selection of meats and cheeses.  There is also a pharmacy.
